reviews: Fabulous boutique hotel with a "Butterfly" theme. From the time we entered the foyer the staff were very friendly and helpful. We had a really nice room with a small balcony. The bed and bedding was of good quality and the rain shower in the well planned bathroom a treat. Breakfast choice was good and easy to enjoy. Will definitely recommend this hotel to our friends and will stay there when we visit Paris again. Great location near Eurostar station, a short walk to galleries Lafayette and close to the Metro to get to all the other spots we wanted to visit during our stay. Excellent Value !! 6 stars !!!

This hotel is almost exactly halfway between Gare d' Est and Gare d' Nord (excuse spelling). There is a food store three doors down. The breakfast buffet was delicious and very filling. The staff was very helpful answering some local travel questions. T was able to reserve a room at a very large discount. Not sure how long these will last as travelers emerge from COVID-19 lock-downs.

We needed to get to the train station easily in the morning with quite a bit of luggage so we bit the bullet and booked this hotel as it is walking distance to Gare du Nord. My daughter who lives in Paris was a bit sceptical as she thinks that this arrondissement is a bit rough.
The hotel is not rough at all. In fact it was lovely. We scored an upgrade - dont know why and really appreciated the additional room with the luggage. We found a lovely restaurant/pub nearby with a delightful waitress. I think this would be a lovely hotel to stay in if it was sunny as there is a gorgeous central seating area for breakfast. It was raining when we were there. Breakfast was included and that was a big bonus as well.
The staff were helpful and stored our luggage for us for the day we arrived and also served us some drinks after dinner.

Excellent staff they are ready for all needs to make your stay as pleasant as possible. Breakfast was rich and many choices to choose from. Room was super clean with daily room service.
Coffee is available at anytime

We chose this hotel for its proximity to both Gare de lEst and Gare du Nord and it was about a 5-10 minute easy walk to both.

It was a very nice boutique hotel. Our room faced the courtyard and was very quiet. The room was really nicely decorated and had everything we needed  including a kettle. The breakfast was very good with lots of choice. Very friendly and helpful staff.

Would recommend.

Have just spent 3 nights in this hotel and loved it. Staff helpful and friendly. Breakfasts good and loved our room too. The Spa was not open but was this was not a problem for us.
Loved the boutique/quirky decor and excellent location.
Would totally recommend

Lovely boutique hotel a short stroll from Gare du Nord & Gare dEst. Our room was nice, the buffet breakfast was fantastic too. The lounge is nice, but wasnt often available during our stay due to doubling up as a conference suite. We didnt manage to make it down to the spa, so cannot comment on that (but it sounds nice), but we enjoyed some afternoon drinks in the bar area instead! There is free wifi and the staff are friendly and helpful. Check out time was a very accommodating 12 noon.
There is a fantastic indoor market just around the corner (less than 10 seconds walk). Finally, If you are staying here and looking for a good quality & value restaurant, then give Mamagoto (next door) a try! (See my review of it on this website)

Really good cosy little hotel , the perfect base from which to explore all that Paris has to offer.
The beds are very comfortable and bedding is clean and plentiful .
I got two good night's sleep .
The hotel is very quiet , despite being located near the largest Paris main line Train  station the Gare Du Nord.
The staff are very friendly and I was made to feel very welcome.
The Breakfast is sensational 10out of 10, great selection of very tasty food and fruit juices,tea and coffee.proof that France lives up to its reputation as being the best place in the world for tasty food.
My only slight concern was a lack of a mini bar in my room , But overall I would totally recommend this hotel to anyone coming to Paris , I stayed with my wife , I think it's particularly suitable for couples

Excellent family run hotel. Staff were so friendly and helpful. Breakfast was perfect for our needs. When we needed advise on local places to visit or travelling on trains to Disneyland or around the Paris Metro, they wrote it down clearly for us. We would reccomend this hotel to anyone. It is a 5 minute walk from Garde de Nord station, which is on the direct line from CDG airport. So Easy to locate.

What a lovely hotel. So conveniently situated within an easy 10 minute walk from Gare du Nord. The hotel staff were excellent and the room was spotless and well equipped. The dining room staff were very helpful especially when it came to getting us gluten free bread etc for breakfast. There was plenty of choice and (my particular favourite) the option of having a pot to make your tea in! It is an easy walk to the metro at Gare de L'Est or as we did, walking everywhere. The Sacre Coeur isn't too far to walk with the beauty of Monmartre near enough on your doorstep. I wouldn't hesitate to recommend and hope to return once the Notre Dame is reopened.

Highly recommend this hotel. A short walking distance from Gard de Nord (Eurostar) and then well placed for a short walk to Sacre Couer/Montmartre or plenty of Metro stations to reach other landmarks in Paris.
The hotel staff were warm and welcoming and always said good morning/evening whenever they passed you.
The hotel is down a quiet side street, it is very clean and well kept. The reception area smells wonderful and the rooms were well kept/cleaned and smelt wonderful too.
We stayed on the 5th floor facing onto the street, a small balcony with table and chairs. The bed was so comfortable and the room and bathroom had everything you would need. We did seem to struggle with the speed of the Wi-Fi at times especially in the evening. Good 4g signal.
Breakfast area was warm and cozy and had a huge selection of warm/continental. Plenty of different drinks and buffet style. In the evening there was self serve warm drinks should you need to warm up (quite cold whilst we were there). Hotel was well heated.
There is a brilliant local supermarket a couple of doors down stocking anything else you might need.
Perfect Hotel!!!

Booked 2 rooms for a family/ friends get together and to see some of the sites of Paris , this is a lovely hotel , well priced , great breakfast and close to the 2 main rail stations , virtually 3 minutes walk to each of them . Safe area with plenty of Restaurants and bars in the area , in fact the restaurant next door( Mamagoto ) is stunning , more about that in another review .rooms were smallish but this Paris afterall , staff were very attentive and provided great service including a private car to the airport early in the morning . Cant fault the hotel would certainly re book

The hotel is lovely. The reception staff were very friendly. The room was very chic with a juliette balcony.
The breakfast was plentiful with helpful staff. I would love to return. The location is easy to find from the station. Please give it a try.

A great Hotel and Excellent Value. Choosing a hotel in which to stay in Paris is always going to be difficult with the sheer volume of choice.
After much research and after settling an a budget, an extensive list narrowed was down to Hotel Mademoiselle.
We travelled from the UK by Eurostar and the location is perfect for the station. It is situated just off a busy Main Street down a little side road and we found it to be very peaceful and quiet, with a tiny amount of traffic actually passing the hotel compared to other nearby roads.
We booked directly with the hotel as this was the best value and the free breakfast was far better, with so much more choice than we had expected.
We loved the area and the main attractions were walkable - if you dont mind getting a few thousand steps in.
Lots of great bars and restaurants within easy walking distance. A great little restaurant a couple of doors down and a fabulous indoor food market on the corner of the street.
Its very difficult to find anything to fault the hotel for. We will definitely stay again.

Room on the first floor, clean and plenty of space. Very friendly staff, luggage taken care of. Comfy bed, lots of pillows, big tv with streaming options. Wifi is good. Montmartre is a short walk away, but we even went to the louvre and beyond on foot (weather was nice). Conveniently located near gare du nord and gare de l'est (less than 10 minutes walk). Breakfast very good, lots of choice, fresh products, well catered for and looked after by the staff.

We had a lovely stay in this hotel that is within easy walking distance of Gare du Nord. Very central too. Could see Eiffel Tower from bedroom window. Clean hotel, lovely comfortable beds with nice linen. Good quality range of toiletries are on offer too. Breakfast was lovely, great range of food to suit all tastes. All the staff were very friendly & nothing was too much bother.

Stayed for a long weekend to go to a match at the Stade and travelled via Eurostar.

The hotel was excellent. it is on a side street 5 minutes from the station. We had a courtyard room which gave us a silent sleep in lovely big bed. Reception and bar staff were friendly and helpful.

Many good eating options nearby.

Our stay at Hotel Mademoiselle was exceptionally pleasant in every way! We had chosen the hotel mainly because of its perfect location near the Gare de l`Est in a quiet side street, but then were very surprised by the special atmosphere of the hotel! Room beautifully furnished with high bed comfort, well equipped bathroom. Varied, quality breakfast, which is always freshly replenished. Exceptionally friendly and helpful staff!

Great service from check in to check out, there was a bigger selection for breakfast than we expected, staff were lovely, we had to check out very early for the train, the night manager made sure we had breakfast and coffee for us to leave which was something we didnt expect but greatly appreciated!

Staff - professional and helpful, and also warm and welcoming. Clean, well organised and very nice for a woman staying on her own. I felt safe and cared for.
Very nice smell atmosphere --- light and delicate not overpowering or artificial.
Excellent location, 5 minutes from Gare du Nord, and 5 minutes from the nearest metro.
Pleasant decor. Well kept and clean. Quiet road - so no sleep disruption. Dark curtains. Ensuite also nicely designed.
Hot chocolate and hot drinks available in the little dining area as well as the room kettle and cups.
Excellent TV with international stations.

Stayed at the hotel for three nights. All the staff were so friendly and helpful. It has a nice atmosphere and is a short walk from the Garden du Nord. The receptionists gave us good restaurant recommendations and helped us with how to get around Paris and booking trips.

Very friendly staff, everyone was so helpful and polite. Very clean rooms. Breakfast was delicious. Within easy reach of Metro stations and attractions. Reception staff very helpful if you needed directions. Would definitely stay here again.

We stayed here in the first week of January for 5 nights. Upon arival, a very short walk having got the eurostar, we found the reception staff to be pleasant and helpful. The room upon immediate impression was clean but with a few issues.

The TV was receiving no signal and upon inspection at the back of the TV, we found the aerial port ripped out. Not just the cable, but the actual part of the TV was snapped meaning you couldn't actually re connect the aerial cable.
We weren't particularly interested in watching TV as they have the option to stream from your phone with a chromecast type device (free) but informed reception because we didn't want to be blamed for the damage. The reception were apologetic and sent someone up immediately to inspect. That was the last we saw or heard of the issue. As i say, we did specify we weren't bothered about moving but was perhaps expecting some feedback on this issue.

The second fault with the room which i didn't actually report was the main wall socket by the bed physically pulled out of the wall when trying to unplug something, not ideal and potentially a safety issue.

Apart from that, the only real negative with the room was the feeling of needing a fresh. The shower was filled with black mould, the mirror above the sink was heavily chipped and there was a sticker in the bathroom that was peeling off the wall.

These minor issues aside (hence not the full 5 stars), we thoroughly enjoyed our stay here. It's well priced and in a great location for easy access to most things. Don't hesitate about booking here unless you are really wanting higher quality room decor.

Thanks Hotel Madmoiselle

Great location especially if you're arriving in Gare du Nord. The staff is nice and helpful. The room was clean and quiet. Wide range of options at breakfast.
Several delicious dinner options within walking distance.
I will definitely go back and recommend this hotel to friends.

The room was clean and a decent size for a Paris hotel room - good bathroom too although the whole place is a little scuffed around the edges and could probably do with a refurb. The breakfast was very good - all fresh with lots of choice
Ideal location - you can walk to Gare Du Nord in less than 5 minutes and easy to get around Paris using the excellent metro system. There are options to eat and drink nearby

We stayed one night arriving late from Eurostar, the staff were very friendly & accommodating. Very close to both Gares Nord & Est. Very comfortable and beautiful decor in this boutique hotel. The breakfast buffet was very tasty & varied selection. We would recommend this hotel.

We booked two double-rooms for our large family of seven. The hotel was clean, comfortable and a quick walk to the Gare du Nord. While a slightly longer walk to Notre Dame and other sights, totally doable. Excellent breakfast and friendly staff.

The hotel is very nice and clean. Check in is 3pm but they gave me a room at 12pm. The neighborhood is not very Parisian but I always felt safe. There are several restaurants to choose from and its a two minute walk from a train station.

We had an enjoyable stay at the hotel, the room was very quiet, comfortable and spacious. Lovely shower in bathroom, nice toiletries, the bed was extremely comfortable. It was a few minutes from Gare du Nord station and mtro so it was very convenient for us arriving and departing from the UK Eurostar and getting about.

Stayed for three days. A little dated but did not distract from what was a lovely stay. Very clean and desk, catering and cleaning staff were exceptionally friendly and helpful. Breakfast was excellent as well. I would highly recommend a stay there. We booked through Eurostar.

There were some things that were good, the check in was easy and they agreed to order a taxi for me to the airport the next morning, the room is decorated very nicely. But also some not good things, the check out person in the morning was quite rude and didnt speak any English despite this being a tourist hotel advertised as English speaking on their website, the taxi ordered for me was significantly overpriced, and the floor of the shower had a spongey bouncy feel that made me worry there was mold underneath. I would say not worth what I paid, unfortunately.

My friend and I had a wonderful experience at Hotel Madamoiselle. The location was excellent, not too far from Gare Nord and L'est, and a quick walk down charming streets towards Le Marais. There was a charming street around the corner (Rue de Fauborg St. Denis) which is FILLED with restaurants, cafes, bars all day and all night long. Our room was comfortable, we had very nice shower pressure, comfortable bed, and we were upgraded to a suite which was very nice :) The staff were great, the breakfast was lovely, and stayed open later than most hotels (was open until almost 11am!). The rooms were modernized and felt very clean. We both agreed we would absolutely stay here again.

Visited this wonderful boutique hotel again this summer. Very conveniently located a short walk from Gare de Nord and Gare de l'Est, this was our seventh visit. The rooms are very comfortable, with character, and the breakfast amazing. Lots of good places to eat nearby (Montmartre is easily walkable too), and a mini-mart right next door, or the covered (and great) Saint Quentin market just round the corner. Would recommend to any traveller.

Great hotel. Brilliant location less than 5 mins walk from Gare Du Nord. Our room was fab and cleaned every day. Breakfast is superb. The staff are all so helpful. Special mention for Gimini who manages the breakfast - he is so friendly and kind - a lovely man.

I have just returned from a weekend in Paris having stayed once again at the excellent Hotel Mademoiselle. This was my 5th visit over a number of years. The hotel is ideally located less than a 10 minute walk from Gare du Nord. The team at the hotel are all very friendly, efficient and welcoming. The rooms are very well presented and very clean and each morning you have a buffet breakfast with plenty of choices to suit all tastes. Its the first place that I would look to stay whenever visiting Paris.

A1 well pleased, very close to Garde Du nord and Garde du Lest. staff very friendly and nice room. You can get to all of Paris from here, very convenient.breakfast was fine plenty of choice. Would stay there again.

An amazing hotel with lovely staff! The room was very good; everything I needed was there; from soaps to hair dryer, from coffee and tea to a roof terrace (as I requested a smoking room). Cleaned properly every day and breakfast was great.

I dont get why some people complain about the neighborhood. When you stay in the area of Gare du Nord, you should already know the neighborhood isnt great. This is in almost every capital close to central station. You wont have any problems though! The hotel is located in a quiet street, and if you turn right the neighborhood gets better. Im a woman traveling alone and walked around late at night too and had no issues with people whatsoever! If anything, the people were lovely. My French isnt good and people really tried to understand me, or tried to speak English for me, some random person behind me in line even helped me with translation. A lovely man in the street even wished me bon voyage when he saw me with my suitcase. Its also a convenient location; I dont like traveling through Gare du Nord, but walk two streets the other was and theres Gare du lEst (much quieter).

Anyway, back to the hotel: the staff was amazing, so friendly and accommodating! The bed, pillows and sheets felt like heaven and Ive never slept so good in my life! Theres a hair dryer in the bathroom that was very good and the shower was amazing. I also loved that I could make my coffee in the morning in my room. The hotel is quiet, and not many tourists; mainly business people or French people visiting the city. I felt safe and welcome and I will definitely book this hotel again when I return. Then I will also make use of the spa as I didnt get to this time.

I have been to Paris around twenty times over 35 years and this is the best hotel I have stayed at, due to the ambience, friendliness and value. The included breakfast was outstanding as a buffet style but really fresh and tasty. They were really welcoming and helpful.

I found it well overpriced, not impressed with anything but its clean, staff is nice and thats about it, they wouldnt let us check in earlier than 3pm but thats not a big deal, I wouldnt pay more than $99 to $130 a night for this hotel, this price range is very decent for this hotel, if youre paying more than this range do yourself a favor and find something better.

Excellent location 5 minute walk from both Gare Du Nord to the Gare de l'Est train stations! The front office staff was incredibly helpful and friendly. We enjoyed the extensive breakfast selection including scrambled eggs, bacon, crepes, breads, yogurt, fruit, meats, cheeses, pastries, croissants, and fresh juices! They even surprised us with a glass of complimentary champagne and room upgrade for our 1 year wedding anniversary. We really enjoyed this hotel and highly recommend it!

This was a really good hotel for the money. Yet the balcony rooms are very noisy. I know that can't be helped. But what can be helped, is the staff not helping us with directions to the closest subway. I politely asked the way to the subway and the young man folded it back up and said he couldn't help. I know I could have used an app, but I figured a local would be able to help.

Checked out after 2 hours. The area felt dirty & threatening. Not the Paris we were hoping for in this side of town. Recommended not to walk around after 10pm.
The hotel is very basic, not symbolic of a 4 star hotel unfortunately.
Very close & walking distance to Eurostar but that is the only benefit.

We stayed here for a couple of nights in August. It was brilliant. Clean, quiet and a great breakfast. We really liked the location as it felt less touristy than other areas of Paris but so close to Gare Du Nord. Perfect when travelling by Eurostar! The food in the local restaurants was also great. We walked miles and fell in love with Paris and Hotel Mademoiselle. We would certainly return. The only improvement would be a little more information at check in. We weren't told about the spa or the times for breakfast. Otherwise the staff were very helpful and friendly. See you again!

If you are looking for service you will find it here in hotel Mademoiselle, the staff is very friendly and happy to make your stay comfortable. The quality of this hotel is very good, clean rooms, nice decorated breakfast room, very nice SPA and fitness room. The breakfast is very tasty with fresh bread, fresh orange juice, (scrambled) eggs, yoghurts and fresh fruit. I like mademoiselle because it's not a big commercial hotel but a nice small (looks like a boutique) hotel.
The hotel is very good located near Gare du Nord and Gare du l'est, even close to the Metrostation Possionere.

Hotel is located very close to Gare du Nord, which was perfect as we were travelling on Eurostar.
When we arrived at the hotel we were provided with a warm welcome from a very professional reception.
The room was very big and the bed was very comfortable.
I can't remember, but I don't think it had a fridge which would have been nice.
The breakfast was amazing and the breakfast staff were very attentive and dealt with all our requests immediately.
Lovely hotel, great staff and a great location.

So happy with this booking.
The staff were so friendly and helpful. The location is perfect and the rooms were very clean. Breakfast was great. Would stay here again and highly recommend it to friends and family!

My mom and I booked 7 nights at the Hotel Mademoiselle Nov. 2021 and we had an amazing experience from the very beginning. We arrived well before check due to our flight and while the room was not ready yet we were offered bottles of water and a comfortable place to lounge while we waited. We only had a short wait and then were off to our room.

We had a room with a lovely view of the interior courtyard; it was spacious for Paris with a nice bed, closet, and desk area. There were also 2 large sets of windows that opened. The bathroom was very well appointed the shower/tub was larger than i expected and had a full size window that opens for air flow.

All the staff that we encountered were very nice. They could answer all of our questions knowledgably and quickly. They printed our boarding passes for us and had a taxi waiting to take us the airport in the middle of the night.

The breakfast that was offered was well worth it and made for a relaxing was to start each day of exploring!

Overall it was a great stay and we are in the process of booking the Hotel Mademoiselle again for Nov. 2022!

Nice, cosy hotel. Rooms even on the street side were very quitisme, all decorated very Nicole and very good breakfast. Staff very friendly and helpfull. Will come back ,next time we are in Paris. A little gem in the french Capital. Love the little matches

Every thing was good. Specially the freeparking! Good breakfast, beautifull atmosphere, very friendly staff, happy with the airco, perfect room. Close to metro Poisonniere. Nice possibility to use your breakfast at the patio

The rooms were lovely and clean and well equipped. Breakfast very good. Service was brilliant. They couldnt do enough to help. Central location and very close to the Eurostar station. I highly recommend this hotel. Only one issue we had was with the air conditioning and they sorted it immediately ( it was probably our fault anyway!)

The hotel was very good. We all really enjoyed ourselves once we got the hitch sorted out with the right bedroom. .. and were offered a couple of glasses of champagne free for the hassle. I would have preferred if this information had been passed on rather than haggle with reception at our departure!

Close to Gare de Nord, very handy when arriving on Eurostar, but walk the other way down the quiet street and youll find good restaurants, a metro station and an easy walk down Rue La Fayette straight into the centre. We stayed for 9 nights in very hot weather. The hotel was our oasis, the courtyard was always cool and the air con worked well inside. Rooms higher up have more light and views (on the front) but courtyard is quieter. We preferred front but its personal choice. The breakfast is varied, fresh and tasty. But most of all the staff are excellent, very friendly and accommodating, from reception to housekeeping, all top notch!

Hotel Mademoiselle is in a great spot, close to the Gare du Nord and the Gare de l'Est and within walking distance of many Parisian attractions. The room was pleasant, clean and comfortable, and the staff went out of their way to be helpful.

Near Gare du Nord an exellent stay for a weekend /week
trip. Nice hotel, good service. clean, and a good breakfast.
Staff is very helpful and location is in centre of Paris . Metro at short distance of the hotel.

I went back and forth on whether to reserve Hotel Mademoiselle or a fancier boutique hotel for 3x the price. I am so glad I decided on Hotel Mademoiselle -- we had a suite for us and our two teenaged kids, and although the rooms were small, they were extremely comfortable. The beds and bedding were very comfortable, and the bathroom had an amazing rainfall shower and fluffy towels. There was an espresso machine in the room. The breakfast buffet available in the hotel was very good with lots of selection, and kids (under 18) eat free. The staff was very helpful, and the location near Gare du Nord and Gare de l'Est is quite convenient. We enjoyed getting to know the nearby neighborhoods as well. Great value.

We had a lovely stay at the Hotel Mademoiselle. If arriving on Eurostar the location couldn't be better and we also needed to travel to the Stade de France for a concert so the hotel was ideal. The room was clean and comfortable and the staff on reception were very helpful with recommendations of places to visit and travel info. We didn't make use of the spa as we had a lot to fit in!

The hotel is fantastically located a short walk from the train station. Was an excellent base for sightseeing in Paris. Our room on the top floor was comfortable and very clean. The staff are all lovely and friendly. Breakfast was plentiful and very good. The only complaint was that I had booked four months ago and requested a private one hour use of the spa. We were extremely disappointed to discover on arrival that our slot had been allocated to other guests instead. We never got to see or use the facilities. The reception staff very kindly tried to accommodate us with an alternative however this was not convenient as was on the morning of our departure. We did enjoy a glass each of complimentary champagne in the bar.
All in all a very enjoyable stay and would book again.

Location is key located between gare du Nord and Gare de l'Est (only 5 mn walk)
Room very confortable, with air conditionning. The room was actually cool on arrival.
Front desk reception staff members very nice and welcoming, always happy to help.
Breakfast full of fresh products- very tasty.
Interieur design is very beautiful and original

We had an overall great experience staying at the hotel. Probably the best bed of all hotels we were staying, with high, wide and hard mattress and just the right size and softness of pillows that allow for restful nigh after long sightseeing days. Breakfast is wonderful with lots of options for everyone and even little patio sitting area for smokers. Hydro massage bed in the spa that is free for guests to use from 10-noon is awesome, relaxing experience. Hotel is very conveniently located to Gare du Nord and Eurostar and everyone in the hotel is friendly, courteous, and eager to help. Overall, a fantastic stay!

Hotel Mademoiselle has it all: a brilliant location (especially when one arrives by Eurostar), quiet and beautifully appointed rooms, delightful breakfast. But most importantly it has what many other hotels lack: staff who are not only unfailingly helpful and courteous, but who work seamlessly as a team. We arrived late in the evening and discovered to our disappointment that due to a misunderstanding the room did not have the facilities we believed to have requested. The concierge was unable to offer a solution immediately due to the hotel being fully booked, but assured us that the day staff would be able to help. When we came down the next morning we were prepared to explain the issue again, but upon mentioning our room number only found to our amazement that the day staff were fully informed. This happened repeatedly throughout our stay - handovers between staff only meant that a different person was at the desk, not that the thread of the conversation was broken. Huge congratulations to such an extraordinary team - and to the management who clearly see value in not only carefully choosing the staff, but more importantly in investing in training. We will definitely come back.

A really charming hotel in an excellent location for the Metro, Gare du Nord and other transport links.
We stayed for 3 nights/4 days whilst visiting for RG tennis. As our timeframe was somewhat tight and we also wanted to visit some Paris attractions the reception staff assisted us daily with travel route planners, to save us getting lost and loosing valuable time!
The breakfasts were delicious, and always served with a smile.
Beautifully presented the bedrooms and dining areas are first class.
I would highly recommend this little gem if you are travelling to Paris, which was in a peaceful setting for a great nights sleep.
I hope to return again very soon. Thank you for your wonderful service, we really enjoyed our stay.

Perfect hotel for a city break. It is situated close to Gare du Nord (or de LEst) so is easy to walk from the Eurostar and to jump on the metro.

The best part is the staff, the reception staff were so friendly, very helpful and attentive. We came in late a few evenings and they asked us how our French was coming (gave us a much need lesson) and gave us some complimentary water!

The breakfast has a good range of choice, it is not gourmet but ideal to start the day and rare to find a hotel in Paris with breakfast.

The rooms are spacious and the showers are really good. Could do with a lick of paint here and there but all good generally.

The spa is also free for a few hours in the morning for guests and is really relaxing for half an hour or so before you go out to explore.

This hotel was super cute and on a quaint little street not far from the action but still a quiet enough area. Everything was super walkable, or accessible by train (the Guard de Nord is extremely close). Lots of great food and drink options within a 5-10 minute walk as well. The staff was super friendly, a nice breakfast spread each morning and an adorable courtyard to sit and drink your coffee or have an evening cocktail. Great vibes all around, would recommend this hotel to others visiting Paris.

5 mins walk from Gare du Nord, I half expected a compromise in quality for the location but we were delighted with the quality of the hotel in general and the warmth of welcome from the staff in particular. There are plenty of restaurants nearby (Mamagoto 2 doors away is excellent too) and metro at Gare do Nord or Poisonniere are easy walks. The private session in the spa at the hotel was included in our rate and was a highlight. Sauna, steam, and hydro bed massage- ideal after a hard days sightseeing. Comfy bed, quiet, good shower, overall we highly recommend this friendly and hospitable hotel to anyone.

Great location, very close by the station Gare du Nord, and several metro stations nearby. Clean rooms, great breakfest, but what makes this hotel is the very friendly staff. Always willing to help to make our stay so pleasant as possible.. We had a great stay and will certainly come back!

We stayed in the Hotel for two nights over the Easter Break. The room was small but very clean. The breakfast was above average.
We most liked the very friendly employees working on the reception. They adressed all questions and helped us to make our stay in Paris unforgetable.

Just came back from a quick trip to Paris taking my daughter for the first time.
Can't fault the hotel, very close to Gare Du Nord so super easy from Eurostar. Very friendly staff and nice clean modern room.
Would happily recommend.

First time in Paris, had a wonderful time ....
Hotel was excellent, helpful staff, location was great,rooms and breakfast was fabulous.
Enjoyed my stay...
Moulin Rouge show was one of the highlights aswell as The Sacre Coer.

This hotel is in a great location, only a 5 minute walk from Gare Du Nord Station. Good for getting around the city and the staff are excellent. Rooms very comfortable and a very good breakfast. This was our second visit and we will certainly be back.

Perfect spotless Hotel in a local location near metro and bus links.

Huge beautiful breakfast.

Extremely welcoming and nice staff.

Room Perfect and relaxing.

100 % could NOT fault it in anyway..

Totally safe surroundings..

Lots of great local restaurants catering for both locals and visitors..

We stayed here for 6 nights. Location is perfect next to the train station for the day trips we took outside the city. The rooms were spacious, clean and comfortable. The staff was super helpful. The breakfast was great. The spotty internet service was a big problem. We were unable to get reliable internet.

This is a lovely hotel, perfectly placed in a quiet side street, only minutes from Gare du nord station and all its connections. Beautifully clean, very friendly and helpful staff, with a fantastic spa in the basement to relax and unwind in. Breakfast was delicious, plentiful and well presented.

Excellent service and clean room. The serving staff at breakfast were so helpful and the breakfast buffet selection was great. Nothing was too much trouble and we left our luggage on the last day. We will definitely be staying again on our return.

This hidden gem was the perfect spot for us. Breakfast buffet was the best, fresh croissants and baguettes plus fresh fruit everyday. My husband and I stayed for 6 days, walking distance to train station and metro, by Gard de Noord. Rooms are exceptionally large compare to European standards, great shower, they do have lifts which is great. They also have spa and sauna rooms. Customer service was phenomenal, everyone spoke English and are very helpful. I would have given this a 5 star rating except their internet was crappy.

This hotel was booked as part of a treat for my husband and I from our children.
What a lovely surprise it was to be in such a superb place. Hotel Mademoiselle is in a good position close to the Gard du Nord station, due to mobility problems we took a taxi but I'm sure it is easily reached on foot. The hotel is welcoming, clean and has a lovely atmosphere. A lift is available to the bedrooms. Our room looked out onto the street and the traditional buildings opposite with their iron railed windows which I loved. The bed was large and comfortable and the bathroom had a very efficient shower. There is a bar available on the ground floor and a pretty area to enjoy the breakfast which was plentiful with lots of choice . The very best of this Hotel is the staff. They are pleasant, always available and good humoured in all our dealings with them. A very special shout out to Antoine who calmed my panic when I thought I'd lost our tickets to an event and went to great lengths to try and sort the problem out for me. I found them later and he was amused but showed no frustration about the amount of his time I'd taken up! Antoine is a star. We would like to thank him and in fact all the staff for making our stay such a pleasant one. We would definitely recommend Hotel Mademoiselle and would return again once travel health regulations allow it.

Helpful staff, nice, well decorated rooms and a great spa. Super breakfast in a beautiful courtyard setting. There were lots of healthy choices available everyday such as cereals, yogurts, all kinds of breads and fruits as well as the traditional goodies such as eggs, bacon, meats. Also a wine and champagne bar. Definitely recommended!

We had a wonderful stay here last week. Its perfectly positioned walking distance from both Gare Nord & Gare LEst. The rooms are a good size for Paris. Breakfast offered a superb selection and the best bit was the INCREDIBLE staff who simply couldnt have done more to make our stay any more perfect. The private spa is a lovely touch too

This was our first trip to Paris (from Ireland) and we stayed at Hotel Mademoiselle. The hotel is a short walk from the Gard Du Nord train station, it is located in a small quiet street. The rooms are small but really well presented and so clean, faultless really. The breakfast is plentiful and always well replenished. Breakfast runs until 10.30am and even when we arrived to eat at 10.15 the wonderful lady in the breakfast room was attentive and continued to bring fresh juices, bread, cheese, meats, smoked salmon, pastries etc so a big shout to the staff in the breakfast room. The reception desk staff were so helpful and polite throughout our 5 day stay. If we return to Paris we will definitely stay again and will be recommending the hotel to friends, family etc who are planning a Paris trip. Thank you to all the staff at the hotel for your wonderful services, from cleaning our room to supplying breakfast and for helpful directions and smiles from the front desk staff. Also worth noting the hotel is surrounded by many supermarkets that are reasonably priced.

Excellent hotel close to Gare du Nord (12 minutes walk). Super friendly staff. Very clean and nicely decorated. Quiet street. Good breakfast includes eggs. Only negative is WIFI weak. Manager said they reduced bandwidth due to Covid so I expect this will get sorted as business picks back up. Will stay here again next time Im in Paris.

Lovely stay. A warm welcome at check-in. Beautiful and cozy rooms, nice and quit location. Close to public transport and nice restaurants. Only negative was the beds, they were a bit to hard for our taste. Coffee and tea available at the room. Easy check-in, good communication in english
We would love to come back

I have found myself stranded in Paris due to missed train (blocked roads). Coming to hotel Mademoiselle and being welcomed by Assane was a real relief! Such kindness and warmth is rare, he is a real asset to the establishment!
Excellent stay, highly recommended

we stayed here a few years back & returnded as it left such a geat memory for us . Amazing stay made special by the staff here It may be a bit too central for some but we love that and the vibrancy that comes with it .

Everything in this hotel is superb, value for money, cleanliness. The staff could not be more helpful. Everybody was excellent but a special thank you to Garmial at breakfast for his good humour and excellent service.

I booked a single room but was presented with a spacious room with Juliet balcony and beautiful decorative details. The hotel is quiet which is a miracle considering it's right in the centre of the city. You practically fall out of Gare du Nord and into the hotel. It has a big atrium where you can have breakfast, the breakfast itself was a dream for someone who loves croissants and pain au chocolat. On top of that the room was well AC'd and don't even get me started on the good water pressure I got in the shower. It's the perfect place for a trip to Paris.

Great little hotel. Walking dinstance from Gare du Nord and the lovely street in the 9th arrondissement. Small but very clean rooms with good beds. Very friendly and professional staff. We had a great stay.

Stylish and warm boutique hotel just 5 minute walk away from Gare du Nord and Gare de L'Est.

Rooms were nice and we had a nice view on the Parisian style buildings on the other side of the street.

from the hotel you can easily walk to the Le Marais neighbourhood and Canal St. Martin which are both very nice areas.

Breakfast was not very special and it took a long time before we got served. But I guess this is due to Corona and that in normal times there is a buffet where you can help yourself.

I did not use the spa so cannot comment on that.

Will be back!

I spent three nights in this well located hotel
The team was warm and really helpful. Also, sanitizer and masks are available for customers.
The room was of decent size for a hotel downtown.
Top notch quality matress!
I highly recommend this hotel.

Within walking distance of the Gare du Nord, in a road appropriately called the 'street of small hotels'! The hotel frontage is very small - so is the rest of it - tall and narrow, built around a small courtyard. Rooms are small but well equipped, and the breakfast buffet is - by French standards at least - quite reasonable (scrambled eggs, bacon and sausage). Very helpful staff at Reception.

Great place to visit Paris, clean romantic rooms, amazing staff, good breakfastbuffet! Love this place, 5stars! This hotel is close to Gare du Nord train and Metro on walking distance. A lot of restaurants surrounding the hotel even a great market with oysters and wines. A supermarket next to the hotel.

This is the second time we stayed in this hotel and we were again very satisfied.
Location and Service are very good.
From the Gare de lEst you can easily walk to the hotel
As last time we had a room to the inner court that was very calm.

Nothing to complain. Very nice staff, small but very pleasant rooms with a very good breakfast. Is in short walking distance to the gare de l'est and gare du nord, in a nice little street. I would love to stay there again

We only had one night in Paris, and needed to hit the sights prior to our check in time, and the reception staff at the hotel were very friendly and allowed us to store our case until we came back to the hotel later that evening. We also had use of the comfortable lounge after our check out time and prior to our departure on the Eurostar the following evening.

A very nice, stylish hotel, conveniently situated, we would definitely stay again if we came back to Paris.

This was my first visit to France let alone Paris and I definitely picked the right hotel. Within easy walking distance from Gare du Nord we found the hotel in a back street location which left a bit to be desired. The frontage looks a little run down which concerned me, but as soon as you walk through the front door, youre in a clean, well presented reception area with an extremely well presented, polite, efficient, humorous, English speaking receptionist. I understand that not all reception staff speak as good English as the young man we encountered. All the staff we encountered were exceptionally polite and couldnt do enough to make our stay enjoyable. In fact, Id go as far to say that they were more than happy to go out of their way for their guests. Our room, (307) was small but large enough. It was clean and tidy and well stocked with everything required for our stay. The bathroom, though very small was also clean but could do with a little TLC, especially in the shower area. The only other area we used was the breakfast room which doubled up as the bar in the evening, but this, as you would expect, was also clean and well presented. Ill definitely go back there again one day.

Conveniently situated right next to Gare Du Nord, near the first day lunch place'Brasserie Flodere', and easy to get elsewhere. Just lovely helpful staff which makes all the difference - nothing too much trouble and super friendly. Also great breakfast

We stayed for 3 nights, room was large enough with a really big, comfortable double bed. Bathroom and shower (not walk-in) was sizeable. The staff, all of them are excellent, nothing is too much. The two restaurant recommendations nearby were both superb.
You are located around 10 mins (slow walk) from Gare du Nord, so perfect for Eurostar or airport (with RER connection). There is a food market less than a minute's walk away.
The breakfast is wide ranging, lots of choice, don't think they have evening restaurant option but they will put out a lovely meats / cheese / salmon platter on request, delicious!
After a good days sight seeing, their small bar area is a cosy place to have a couple of drinks before retiring for the evening.
They advertise a spa but we did not use, so cannot comment.
We'll defintely return to this hotel!

Had a short stay at this hotel.
Its clean and comfortable... located close to Gard de Nord and Gard de Est, beaning getting the Metro is convenient...

Access to the gym was disappointing as they whole gym was booked for classes. Also no weights machines.

Breakfast options were good, and athe staff were very polite.

I have rarely come across a boutique hotel as friendly and caring at the same time. They take away all of your cares and worries in the world and help to make your stay with them better than you ever imagined.

The staff is not a staff, they are a family.

A lovely hotel, great location for our visit, superb service throughout especially upon check in and check out, very good value for money, clean throughout and good wifi.
I highly recommend this hotel.

We will be back when we need a hotel in Paris for a short business trip. Business partner was convinced as well. Next time we will try the breakfast, so can't comment on that.
Clean room, bathroom maybe a little too small.

We typically stay at Homeaway/AitBnB type places, but we thought we'd give a hotel a try during our second Paris trip. We are so glad we did. The staff was beyond accommodating. Typically, I get names and I neglected to do so. Every interaction we had with staff was really pleasant/entertaining.

We checked in the morning of 1/1/2020. Our room wasn't ready and the front desk person offered to store our luggage until our room was ready. Within minutes, he found us a room, without our asking, which was an upgrade, at no additional charge. He had a dry sense of humor that my wife and I found entertaining and thought he was very personable. As we waiting for the elevator, we heard a crash noise from inside the elevator shaft and the elevator stopped.. Afraid someone may have fallen, we alerted a staff person passing by. He immediately ran up the stairs and quickly found a housekeeping person had dropped some glass in the elevator. He cleared the issue best as he could then made it a point to escort us to our room and answer any questions we had.

Later that evening, we had occasion to visit the bar/lounge area. The young man working there was beyond nice and had an pleasantly amused air about him, which was very personable. Did we luck out and just happen to run into a few staff personnel who happened to be great? I don't think so. I sense a real effort is being made there. We really enjoyed our brief stay and most likely will stay there again when next in Paris.
